description: Nodes for reading each bit of a byte.

@/read-0.description: Read the least significant bit (0) of a byte.

@/read-7.description: Read bit 7 (most significant bit of byte).

@/example-u16-to-bits.description: Demonstrates reading the boolean value of each of the bits in a 16-bit unsigned integer. Run in debugger.

@/example-byte-to-bits.description: Demonstrates reading the boolean value of each of the bits in a byte. Run in debugger.

@/boolean-bit-to-0-1-string.description: Convert a boolean to its string representation. True becomes "1" and false becomes "0".

@/example-u16-to-bit-string.description: Demonstrates converting a 16-bit unsigned integer into a string representation of its bits. Run in debugger.

name: read-bits
